---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import HeroImage from "@components/HeroImage.astro";
import Description from "@components/Description.astro";
import Table from "@components/Table.astro";
import TableRow from "@components/TableRow.astro";
import PlatformLink from "@components/PlatformLink.astro";

import DescriptionPicture from "@components/DescriptionPicture.astro";

import image1 from "@assets/games/fortnite/picture1.jpg";
import image2 from "@assets/games/fortnite/picture2.jpg";
---

<style>
  :root {
    --header-position-hue: 90%;
  }
</style>

<Layout
  title="cloud361 - Fortnite"
  description="Join cloud on a gaming odyssey like no other. From dominating battlefields to unraveling epic quests, Gummientchen explores pixel realms, leaving no virtual stone unturned."
  heading="Fortnite"
  subheading="FÃ¼r Fortnite"
  minimal="true"
>
  <HeroImage svg="fortnite" fill="true" />
  <Table title="My Stats">
    <TableRow component="Playtime">50 hours (18.08.2023)</TableRow>
    <TableRow component="Platform">Epic Games</TableRow>
    <TableRow component="Playing with">
      <PlatformLink
        linktext="Friends"
        linkhref=""
        iconname="steam"
      />
    </TableRow>
  </Table>
  <Description>
    <p>
      Fortnite, developed by Epic Games, is a groundbreaking free-to-play battle royale game that has taken the gaming world by storm. 
      With its unique building mechanics, vibrant and ever-changing world, and a multitude of cosmetic items to unlock, Fortnite offers 
      an engaging and dynamic gaming experience. Beyond its casual appeal, Fortnite has established 
      itself in the competitive esports scene, hosting major tournaments with substantial prizes. 
      This cultural phenomenon has redefined the battle royale genre, providing players of all levels an 
      exciting and continually evolving adventure on the battlefield.
    </p>

    <p>
      Step into the colorful and dynamic world of Fortnite, a game that has revolutionized the battle royale genre. Developed by Epic Games, 
      Fortnite has become a cultural phenomenon, offering players an exciting and ever-evolving gaming experience. 
      With its free-to-play model, Fortnite has attracted a massive player base of all ages, creating a global gaming community like no other.
    </p>

    <DescriptionPicture
      src={image1}
      alt="Picture of Fortnite"
    />

    <p>
      In Fortnite, you're not just a player; you're a builder, explorer, and warrior all in one. 
      The game's unique building mechanic allows you to construct structures on-the-fly, adding a layer of strategy and creativity to every match. 
      Alongside the standard battle royale mode, Fortnite offers various limited-time events and creative modes, keeping the gameplay fresh and exciting.
    </p>

    <p>
      What sets Fortnite apart is its vibrant and constantly changing world. 
      The island of Fortnite features a mix of natural landscapes, urban environments, 
      and fantastical elements, ensuring each match feels distinct. Players can expect surprises like map changes, 
      new points of interest, and in-game events that shape the narrative of the Fortnite universe.
    </p>

    <p>
      Fortnite's Battle Pass system offers a unique progression experience. 
      By completing challenges and playing matches, you can unlock a 
      plethora of cosmetic items, including skins, emotes, and back bling. 
      This system provides a sense of accomplishment and allows players to showcase their individuality on the battlefield.
    </p>

    <DescriptionPicture
      src={image2}
      alt="Picture of Fortnite"
    />

    <p>
      Fortnite has also made its mark in the competitive gaming scene with the Fortnite World Cup and numerous esports tournaments. 
      These events offer substantial cash prizes and attract the world's best players, solidifying Fortnite's status as a powerhouse in the esports arena.
    </p>

    <p>
      Fortnite is a game that has not only redefined the battle royale genre but has also become a 
      cultural phenomenon in its own right. With its building mechanics, evolving world, and dedication 
      to keeping gameplay fresh, Fortnite continues to captivate players of all skill levels. 
      Whether you're a casual gamer or an aspiring esports pro, Fortnite offers an exhilarating 
      and social gaming experience that transcends traditional boundaries. Join the battle, build 
      your way to victory, and become a part of the Fortnite legacy today!
    </p>
  </Description>
  <Table title="Information about the Game">
    <TableRow component="Developer">Epic Games</TableRow>
    <TableRow component="Publisher">Epic Games</TableRow>
    <TableRow component="Release Date">21.07.2017</TableRow>
    <TableRow component="Genre">Battle Royale</TableRow>
    <TableRow component="Official Website">
      <PlatformLink
        linktext="fortnite.com"
        linkhref="https://www.fortnite.com/"
        iconname=""
      />
    </TableRow>
    <TableRow component="Epic Games store page">
      <PlatformLink
        linktext="Fortnite"
        linkhref="https://store.epicgames.com/en-US/p/fortnite"
        iconname="epicgames"
      />
    </TableRow>
  </Table>
</Layout>
